blue.lapis.methodremapper

Class Remapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • blue.lapis.methodremapper.Remapper

  • public class Remapper
extends Object
    Represents the main remapper that will remap given classes using the provided method mappings.

                         String method)
                  throws IOException
        Gets the mapping (new method name) for the specified method.

        owner - The full qualified owning class of the method in internal format, e.g. java/lang/Object

      • remap

        public byte[] remap(String name)
             throws IOException
        Loads and remaps the given class file using the mappings of this Remapper. This will scan the class hierarchy of the given class for matching mappings and finally remap the method names to their new names. If one of the super classes was not scanned for matching mappings yet it will be queried from the provided ClassProvider.
        Parameters:
        name - The class name to remap
        Returns:
        The remapped class
        Throws:
        IOException - If loading classes from the provider fails

      • remap

        public byte[] remap(byte[] bytes)
             throws IOException
        Remaps the given class file using the mappings of this Remapper. This will scan the class hierarchy of the given class for matching mappings and finally remap the method names to their new names. If one of the super classes was not scanned for matching mappings yet it will be queried from the provided ClassProvider.
        Parameters:
        bytes - The class bytes to read from
        Returns:
        The remapped class
        Throws:
        IOException - If loading classes from the provider fails

      • remap

        public byte[] remap(ClassReader reader)

        Remaps the given class file using the mappings of this Remapper. This will scan the class hierarchy of the given class for matching mappings and finally remap the method names to their new names. If one of the super classes was not scanned for matching mappings yet it will be queried from the provided ClassProvider.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
